# Daily UK Job Search Agent

Python tool: Adzuna API → filter/dedupe → optional LLM score → Telegram digest. Runs daily via GitHub Actions.

## Profile (matching reference — search must cover ALL of this)
- Location: Ilford, London; Greater London or UK remote
- Level: entry-level/graduate; no visa sponsorship; UK right to work
- Salary: £24k–£35k (allow missing salary; full-stack London roles may go slightly higher)
- Track A — Analytics/business: Data Analyst, Business Analyst, Reporting Analyst, Engagement Officer, CRM, Marketing Coordinator
- Track B — Full stack (new): Junior/Graduate Developer, Full Stack Developer, Software Developer, Web Developer
- Skills: Power BI, Excel, CRM campaigns, stakeholder reporting, Python, full-stack (frontend + backend + APIs/databases)
- Step 2: cast a wide net across BOTH tracks + London + remote; filtering comes later

## Build order
One step per change. Test after each step. Flag manual setup (API keys, BotFather, GitHub Secrets).

## Code conventions
- Python 3.11+; `requests` for HTTP; `python-dotenv` for local secrets
- Never commit secrets; use `.env` locally, GitHub Secrets in CI
- Keep modules small: `search_jobs.py`, `filters.py`, `dedupe.py`, `score_jobs.py`, `send_digest.py`, `main.py`
- Plain-language comments; explain errors clearly for a non-technical user
- Minimal scope per step — do not build ahead of the current phase

## GitHub Actions note
Local JSON dedupe won't persist between runs — plan cache or committed state in Phase 5.
